CIDR - Classless inter domain routing
cidr - set os ip's 
8+8+8+8 =32 
Example : 10.0.0.0/32
  *.10.0.0.0/32 -> 10.0.0.0 (1)
  *.10.0.0.0/31 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.1 (2)
  *.10.0.0.0/30 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.3 (4)
  *.10.0.0.0/29 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.7 (8)
  *.10.0.0.0/28 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.15 (16)
  *.10.0.0.0/27 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.31 (32)
  *.10.0.0.0/26 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.63 (64)
  *.10.0.0.0/25 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.127 (128)
  *.10.0.0.0/24 -> 10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.255 (256)
  *.10.0.0.0/23 -> 10.0.1.0 - 10.0.1.255 (512)
  *.10.0.0.0/22 -> 10.0.3.0 - 10.0.3.255 (1024)
      Example :
                10.0.0.0 - 10.0.0.255 - A - 256
                10.0.0.1 - 10.0.1.255 - B - 256
                10.0.2.0 - 10.0.2.255 - C - 256
                10.0.3.0 - 10.0.3.255 - D - 256  -----> (1024)
Formula :
190.0.12.0/27 = 32-27 = 5 = 2 power of 5 
                          = 2*2*2*2*2 = 32
Milestone value :
/32 - 1
/30 - 4
/24 - 256
/16 - 65536

